place.name: BRAUNCEWELL
place.gazetteerText: BRAUNCEWELL-WITH-DUNSBY, or Branswell-with-Dunsby, a parish in Sleaford district, Lincoln; 4½ miles NNW of Sleaford r. station. Post Town, Sleaford. Acres, 3,470. Real property, £4,828. Pop., 112. Houses, 18. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory, united with the vicarage of Anwick, in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £715.* Patrons, alternately the Marquis of Bristol and Mrs. H. Robinson. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
